        "id": 5010
      },
      "writtenOn": "2018-07-03T15:11:28Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "This may sound silly, but let\u0027s try to use as few NEON intrinsics as possible.  They\u0027re incredibly hard to read compared to just writing normal code.  And that way when you do something interesting that can\u0027t be expressed with normal operations (e.g. vld2) it stands out more.\n\nE.g.\n\n   template \u003ctypename T\u003e\n   static T load(const void* ptr) {\n       T val;\n       memcpy(\u0026val, ptr, sizeof(val));\n       return val;\n   }\n\n   template \u003ctypename T\u003e\n   static void store(void* ptr, T val) {\n       memcpy(ptr, \u0026val, sizeof(val));\n   }\n\n   ...\n\n   auto xx \u003d load\u003cuint32x4_t\u003e(xy);\n   store(x0, xx \u003e\u003e 18);\n   store(x1, xx \u0026 0x3fff);\n\n   etc.",
      "revId": "b3d0622ab03e971dce3e88660bc515c448cf68cd",
